The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Bhagalpur, Sept. 3 (PTI): Policemen have threatened to launch an agitation to protest the dismissal of two colleagues for dragging a chain-snatcher tied to a motorcycle. 

 The Bihar Police Association and the Bihar Policemens Association have decided to launch a phased agitation to pressure authorities to withdraw the dismissal order.

 New Delhi: Ashesh Prosad Mitra, the Calcutta-educated physicist who had for decades played a key role in steering Indian research in atmosphere physics and climate change science, died on Monday. Mitra died of a kidney problem at AIIMS. He was 81. He is survived by his wife and two daughters.

 New Delhi (PTI): Circuit designer Hermann Tilke arrived in the capital on Monday to assess sites for building a Formula One track. Tilke visited some sites today. He will see more sites again tomorrow (Tuesday), Indian Olympic Association president Suresh Kalmadi said.

 New Delhi (PTI): The gross salary of a person who died in a road mishap has to be considered for calculating compensation by insurance companies, a tribunal has said. The motor accident claim tribunal rejected a companys contention that the courts had to deduct his PF contribution and advance, and other donations while deciding the compensation. All monetary benefits are not to be liable for deduction under the motor vehicles act, it said.

 New Delhi (PTI): Eight robbers have been arrested after a brief gunbattle with police. An Italian pistol and a Korean revolver were seized from them. The arrests came after a tip-off that some people were planning a robbery at a park in Inderpuri on Sunday evening.

 Jammu (PTI): Thirteen kg of explosives was recovered along with arms and ammunition on a tip-off when troops unearthed two hideouts in Reasi and Rajouri districts, official sources have said.




